y:Dutch financial analysts]]\n[[Category:Dutch nonprofit directors]]\n[[Category:Dutch political consultants]]\n[[Category:Dutch political writers]]\n[[Category:Dutch speechwriters]]\n[[Category:Financial economists]]\n[[Category:Foreign policy writers]]\n[[Category:Grand Officers of the Order of Leopold II]]\n[[Category:International Accounting Standards Board members]]\n[[Category:International economists]]\n[[Category:Macroeconomists]]\n[[Category:Members of the House of Representatives (Netherlands)]]\n[[Category:Ministers of Economic Affairs of the Netherlands]]\n[[Category:Ministers of Finance of the Netherlands]]\n[[Category:Ministers of Health of the Netherlands]]\n[[Category:Ministers of Sport of the Netherlands]]\n[[Category:Monetary economists]]\n[[Category:Monetarists]]\n[[Category:Officers of the Order of Orange-Nassau]]\n[[Category:Paul H. Nitze School of Advanced International Studies alumni]]\n[[Category:People from Haarlem]]\n[[Category:People's Party for Freedom and Democracy politicians]]\n[[Category:Public economists]]\n[[Category:State Secretaries for Social Affairs of the Netherlands]]\n[[Category:20th-century Dutch civil servants]]\n[[Category:20th-century Dutch businesspeople]]\n[[Category:20th-century Dutch economists]]\n[[Category:20th-century Dutch male writers]]\n[[Category:20th-century Dutch politicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century Dutch civil servants]]\n[[Category:21st-century Dutch businesspeople]]\n[[Category:21st-century Dutch economists]]\n[[Category:21st-century Dutch male writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Dutch politicians]]\n", "name_user": "Tristan Surtel", "label": "safe", "comment": "links", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hans_Hoogervorst"}
{"title_page": "Derni\u00e8re danse (Indila song)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Derni\u00e8re danse\n| cover      = Derniere danse cover.png\n| alt        =2019\n| border     = yes\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Indila]]\n| album      = [[Mini World (album)|Mini World]]\n| released   = 13 November 2013\n| format     = Digital download\n| recorded   = 2013\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = {{flatlist|Pop\n*[[French pop]]\n*[[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]\n}}\n| length     = {{duration|m=3|s=32}}\n| label      = [[Capitol Music Group]]\n| writer     = [[Indila|Adila Sedra\u00efa]]\n| producer   = [[Skalp]]ovich\n| prev_title = Dreamin\n| prev_year  = 2012\n| next_title = Tourner dans le vide\n| next_year  = 2014\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|K5KAc5CoCuk|\"Derni\u00e8re danse\"|link=no}}}}\n}}\n\"'''Derni\u00e8re danse'''\" (''\"Last dance\"'') is a song recorded by French singer-songwriter [[Indila]]. It served as the first single from her debut album, ''[[Mini World (album)|Mini World]]''. The musical motif is likely sampled from [[Charles Aznavour]]'s song [[Parce Que Tu Crois]].\n\n== Music ==\nThe song is in the key of C minor and in a BPM of 114.\n== Music video ==\n\n=== Background and Possible Synopsis ===\nThe music video was filmed in November 2013 and premiered on 4 December 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chartsinfrance.net/Indila/news-89096.html|title=Indila : d\u00e9couvrez \"Derni\u00e8re danse\", son premier clip apocalyptique (m\u00e0j)|language=French|accessdate=4 December 2013|work=Charts in France}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.melty.fr/indila-derniere-danse-le-clip-devoile-a233382.html|title=Indila : Derni\u00e8re Danse, le clip d\u00e9voil\u00e9|work=Melty|accessdate=4 December 2013|language=French}}</ref> The music video is a short film directed by Sylvain Bressollette.\n\nThis is a drama song which is full of despair and sorrow \"here comes the pain\". Despair may come from loneliness as the singer can be seen holding a picture of someone she longs for. Without him she suffers from low self-esteem \"I\u2019m just a worthless being\", sense of separation from the one she loves: \"without him I\u2019m a bit troubled\", from a painful past \"a last dance to forget my great misery\". It also comes from the fear of confrontation with the darkness. Darkness is represented by the city (rude, pushy man, unforgiving landlord, staring woman in a car) and internally represented in her emotional world by her \"sweet\" torment to find courage, feminine strength, and most of all, self-esteem. She also wants to reconnect with the one she loves or simply with a masculine energy \"try as I might, without you my life is nothing but a meaningless shiny d\u00e9cor\". Thus, she is confronted: \"I\u2019m afraid, is this my turn?\", by the external and internal elements, external and internal storm that hits her and the city. She is fighting with her weaknesses, for she does not want to abandon hope for love and salvation from her misery: \"In all of Paris, I abandon myself and away I fly, fly / a bit of love and I dance{{nbsp}}...\".\n\nThen, in the climax, she realizes she paid off her dues and is fed up with the torment: \"offences I paid in full\".\nShe challenges the world, \"this is my last dance\" to show how great her heart is, how ready for challenge, romance, appreciation of her feminine strength (in the video she faces the storm with loose hair, standing firmly with arms and legs apart). \"Listen to how great my heart is / I\u2019m a child of the world\". She is ready to become mature: leave her childish fears behind (in the video represented by the girl hiding in the car and looking via back window) and make the world realize she is the embodiment of the divine universe: \"I stir the sky, the day, the night, I dance with the wind, the rain.\" In the video she embraces the storm cloud and is elevated to a quiet spot where she is unaffected by its violence and noise. However, there is a catch, because up there the wind steals the photo of the one she was longing for. \nIn the whole song, she seems to transform from a child, to a woman, to a spiritual consciousness: \"In all Paris, I abandon myself and away I fly, fly, fly{{nbsp}}...\".\n\n=== Lyric video ===\nA lyric video was uploaded on the artist's [[Vevo]] channel simultaneously on the release day of the song.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.melty.fr/indila-derniere-danse-la-video-lyrics-devoilee-a227289.html|title=Indila : Derni\u00e8re Danse, la vid\u00e9o lyrics d\u00e9voil\u00e9e|work=Melty|language=French|accessdate=13 November 2013}}</ref> The video starts off with the title and a sketched version of the singer and a fade-out to black after the song finishes. There is also a Germany-only re-release of the music video provided with German subtitles released after the premiere of the original music video.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vevo.com/watch/indila/dernire-danse-german-subtitles/FRUV71400086?gclid=CNXLuYzzgL0CFWT4wgod9SIAoQ|title=Derni\u00e8re Danse (German Subtitles) \u2013 Indila \u2013 Vevo|work=[[Vevo]]}}</ref>\n\n== Chart performance ==\nOn 1 March 2014, it entered the Greek charts at number-one and stayed at the first place for seven weeks.<ref name=\"greekcharts1\"/> On 19 April 2014, it was knocked down to No. 2 by [[Pharrell Williams]]' [[Happy (Pharrell Williams song)|Happy]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/biz/charts/2014-04-19/greece|title=''Billboard'' Greece Digital Songs \u2013 April 19, 2014|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=12 April 2014|accessdate=10 July 2014}}</ref> It reclaimed No. 1 the following week,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/biz/charts/2014-04-26/greece|title=''Billboard'' Greece Digital Songs \u2013 April 26, 2014|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=19 April 2014|accessdate=10 July 2014}}</ref> and remained there for another five weeks, totaling at thirteen weeks at No. 1.<ref name=\"greekcharts4\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/biz/charts/2014-05-31/greece|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|title=Greece Digital Songs \u2013 May 31, 2014}} {{subscription required}}</ref>\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n=== Weekly charts ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"|Chart (2014)\n!scope=\"col\"|Peak<br>position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" {{singlechart|Austria|72|artist=Indila|song=Derni\u00e8re danse}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" {{singlechart|Flanders|5|artist=Indila|song=Derni\u00e8re danse}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" {{singlechart|Wallonia|2|artist=Indila|song=Derni\u00e8re danse}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Belgium Digital Songs (''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'')<ref name=\"belgiancharts1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/biz/charts/2014-03-08/belgium|title=Belgium Digital Songs \u2013 March 8, 2014|date=8 March 2014|accessdate=10 June 2014}} {{subscription required}}</ref>\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"| 4\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" {{singlechart|Czech Republic|24|week=27|year=2014}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" {{singlechart|Czechdigital|53|year=2014|week=33|accessdate=August 19, 2014}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" {{singlechart|France|2|artist=Indila|song=Derni\u00e8re danse}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" {{singlechart|Germany2|47|artist=Indila|song=Derni\u00e8re danse|songid=1216653|accessdate=16 May 2019}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Greece Airplay Chart ([[International Federation of the Phonographic Industry|IFPI]])<ref>{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140417074230/http://www.ifpi.gr/airplay_el.html|url=http://www.ifpi.gr/airplay_el.html|title=Airplay Chart|language=Greek|publisher=[[International Federation of the Phonographic Industry]]|archivedate=17 April 2014}}</ref>\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Greece Digital Songs (''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'')<ref name=\"greekcharts1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/biz/charts/2014-03-01/greece|title=Greece Digital Songs \u2013 March 1, 2014}} {{subscription required}}</ref>\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" {{singlechart|Israelairplay|1|artist=Indila|song=Derni\u00e8re danse|year=2014|week=13|date=23/03/2014-29/03/2014|accessdate=30 March 2014}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Lebanon Top 20<ref>http://www.olt20.com/Indila#fragment-2&panel1-3</ref>\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"| 3\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" {{singlechart|Poland|3|year=2014|chartid=1354|accessdate=2014-07-21}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|Poland ([[Polish Music Charts|Video Chart]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bestsellery.zpav.pl/airplays/pozostale/archiwum.php?year=2014&typ=tv&idlisty=1396#title|title=Top 5 Airplay TV|work=[[Polish Video Chart]]|publisher=[[ZPAV]] |accessdate=8 February 2017}}</ref>\n| align=center| 2\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|Romania ([[Airplay 100 (Romania)|Airplay 100]])<!--Please do not change this to Romanian Top 100 or Media Forest. The Airplay 100 is Romania's national singles chart from 2012 onwards. For further information, see WP:GOODCHARTS--><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kissfm.ro/podcasturi/2496|title=Airplay 100 \u2013 30 martie 2014|publisher=[[Kiss FM (Romania)|Kiss FM]]|language=Romanian|accessdate=31 March 2020|date=30 March 2014}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|2\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"{{Single chart|Romaniaradioairplay|1|year=2014|week=13|song=Derni\u00e8re danse|artist=Indila|accessdate=2 July 2018|publishdate=24 March 2014}}\n|-\n{{Single chart|Romaniatvairplay|1|year=2014|week=17|song=Derni\u00e8re danse|artist=Indila|accessdate=3 July 2018|publishdate=21 April 2014|rowheader=true}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" {{singlechart|Slovakia|14|week=40|year=2014}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" {{singlechart|Slovakdigital|76|year=2014|week=28|accessdate=July 15, 2014}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" {{singlechart|Switzerland|15|artist=Indila|song=Derni\u00e8re danse}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Turkey (''[[Number 1 TV|Number 1]] Top 40'')<ref name=\"Number1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.numberone.com.tr/tr/muzik/number-one-top-40/index.1.html|publisher=[[Number 1 TV]]|title=Number One FM Top 40 Playlist|accessdate=23 July 2014}} {{subscription required}}</ref>\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1\n|-\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Year-end charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"|Chart (2014)\n!scope=\"col\"|Position\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Belgium ([[Ultratop]] Wallonia)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ultratop.be/fr/annual.asp?year%3D2014%26cat%3Da |title=Archived copy |accessdate=28 December 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150102163859/http://www.ultratop.be/fr/annual.asp?year=2014&cat=a |archivedate=2 January 2015 }}</ref>\n|3\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|France ([[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique|SNEP]])<ref>http://www.snepmusique.com/actualites-du-snep/le-top-5-albums-et-titres-de-lannee-2014/</ref>\n|4\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|Israel ([[Media Forest]])<ref>http://www.mako.co.il/music-news/radio_airplay_chart/Article-ef0dc15a9b4aa41006.htm</ref>\n|7\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Poland ([[Polish Society of the Phonographic Industry|ZPAV]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bestsellery.zpav.pl/aktualnosci.php?idaktualnosci=1152|title=Utwory, kt\u00f3rych s\u0142uchali\u015bmy w radiu \u2013 Airplay 2014|publisher=[[Polish Society of the Phonographic Industry]]|language=Polish|accessdate=21 January 2015}}</ref>\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|20\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Romania (Airplay 100)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kissfm.ro/podcasturi/2813|title=Airplay 100 \u2013 Top of the Year 2014|publisher=[[Kiss FM (Romania)|Kiss FM]]|language=Romanian|accessdate=31 March 2020|date=28 December 2014}}</ref>\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|3\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Ukraine Airplay ([[Tophit]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tophit.ru/en/chart/ukraine/yearly/2014-01-01/all/all|title=Ukrainian Top Year-End Radio Hits (2014)|publisher=[[Tophit]] |accessdate=10 August 2019}}</ref> \n|style=\"text-align:center;\"| 152\n|-\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n== Other versions ==\n* Natacha Andr\u00e9ani performed the song on the third season of the [[The Voice: la plus belle voix|French version]] of ''[[The Voice (TV series)|The Voice]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://videos.tf1.fr/the-voice/extraits/natacha-andreani-interprete-en-direct-la-derniere-danse-indila-8394871.html|title=Natacha Andr\u00e9ani interpr\u00e8te en direct \"La derni\u00e8re danse\" (Indila) pour The Voice|work=[[TF1]]|accessdate=5 April 2014|language=French|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140408034144/http://videos.tf1.fr/the-voice/extraits/natacha-andreani-interprete-en-direct-la-derniere-danse-indila-8394871.html|archivedate=8 April 2014}}</ref>\n* Nicole Cherry impersonated the singer and performed the song on the [[Te cunosc de undeva!|Romanian version]] of the reality show, ''[[Your Face Sounds Familiar]]''.\n*  In 2014, Shirel Bitan performed the song on the third season of the [[The Voice Israel|Israeli version]] of ''The Voice''\n* In 2015, Vladislav Keranov, Jay and F.O. made a BG Hip-Hop comic parody version of the song.\n* The [[Actress|Serbian actress]] [[Jelena Gavrilovic]] impersonated the singer and sang this song on the [[Tvoje lice zvu\u010di poznato (Serbian season 2)|Serbian version of ''Your Face Sounds Familiar'']].\n* In 2016, Kosovan singer Kestrina Blackori performed the song on the 5th season of the [[The Voice of Albania|Albanian version of The Voice]] but didn't score a chair turn.\n* In 2017, French child singer Ilyana Raho-Moussa performed the song on Season 4 of [[The Voice Kids (French TV series)|The Voice Kids France]].\n* In 2019, HIDDN & RudeLies put out a single of this song featuring vocals by [[Ester Peony]], a songstress who has already covered this song in prior performances\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Derniere danse}}\n[[Category:2014 singles]]\n[[Category:2014 songs]]\n[[Category:French-language songs]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Greece]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Israel]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Turkey]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Derni\u00e8re danse\n| cover      = Derniere danse cover.png\n| alt        =2019\n| border     = yes\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Indila]]\n| album      = [[Mini World (album)|Mini World]]\n| released   = 13 November 2013\n| format     = Digital download\n| recorded   = 2013\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = {{flatlist|Pop\n*[[French pop]]\n*[[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]\n}}\n| length     = {{duration|m=3|s=32}}\n| label      = [[Capitol Music Group]]\n| writer     = [[Indila|Adila Sedra\u00efa]]\n| producer   = [[Skalp]]ovich\n| prev_title = Dreamin\n| prev_year  = 2012\n| next_title = Tourner dans le vide\n| next_year  = 2014\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|K5KAc5CoCuk|\"Derni\u00e8re danse\"|link=no}}}}\n}}\n\"'''Derni\u00e8re danse'''\" (''\"Last dance\"'') is a song recorded by French singer-songwriter [[Indila]]. It served as the first single from her debut album, ''[[Mini World (album)|Mini World]]''. The musical motif is likely sampled from [[Charles Aznavour]]'s song [[Parce Que Tu Crois]].\n\n== Music ==\nThe song is in the key of C minor and in a BPM of 114.\n== Music video ==\n\n=== Background and Possible Synopsis ===\nThe music video was filmed in November 2013 and premiered on 4 December 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chartsinfrance.net/Indila/news-89096.html|title=Indila : d\u00e9couvrez \"Derni\u00e8re danse\", son premier clip apocalyptique (m\u00e0j)|language=French|accessdate=4 December 2013|work=Charts in France}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.melty.fr/indila-derniere-danse-le-clip-devoile-a233382.html|title=Indila : Derni\u00e8re Danse, le clip d\u00e9voil\u00e9|work=Melty|accessdate=4 December 2013|language=French}}</ref> The music video is a short film directed by Sylvain Bressollette.\n\nThis is a drama song which is full of despair and sorrow \"here comes the pain\". Despair may come from loneliness as the singer can be seen holding a picture of someone she longs for. Without him she suffers from low self-esteem \"I\u2019m just a worthless being\", sense of separation from the one she loves: \"without him I\u2019m a bit troubled\", from a painful past \"a last dance to forget my great misery\". It also comes from the fear of confrontation with the darkness. Darkness is represented by the city (rude, pushy man, unforgiving landlord, staring woman in a car) and internally represented in her emotional world by her \"sweet\" torment to find courage, feminine strength, and most of all, self-esteem. She also wants to reconnect with the one she loves or simply with a masculine energy \"try as I might, without you my life is nothing but a meaningless shiny d\u00e9cor\". Thus, she is confronted: \"I\u2019m afraid, is this my turn?\", by the external and internal elements, external and internal storm that hits her and the city. She is fighting with her weaknesses, for she does not want to abandon hope for love and salvation from her misery: \"In all of Paris, I abandon myself and away I fly, fly / a bit of love and I dance{{nbsp}}...\".\n\nThen, in the climax, she realizes she paid off her dues and is fed up with the torment: \"offences I paid in full\".\nShe challenges the world, \"this is my last dance\" to show how great her heart is, how ready for challenge, romance, appreciation of her feminine strength (in the video she faces the storm with loose hair, standing firmly with arms and legs apart). \"Listen to how great my heart is / I\u2019m a child of the world\". She is ready to become mature: leave her childish fears behind (in the video represented by the girl hiding in the car and looking via back window) and make the world realize she is the embodiment of the divine universe: \"I stir the sky, the day, the night, I dance with the wind, the rain.\" In the video she embraces the storm cloud and is elevated to a quiet spot where she is unaffected by its violence and noise. However, there is a catch, because up there the wind steals the photo of the one she was longing for. \nIn the whole song, she seems to transform from a child, to a woman, to a spiritual consciousness: \"In all Paris, I abandon myself and away I fly, fly, fly{{nbsp}}...\".\n\n=== Lyric video ===\nA lyric video was uploaded on the artist's [[Vevo]] channel simultaneously on the release day of the song.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.melty.fr/indila-derniere-danse-la-video-lyrics-devoilee-a227289.html|title=Indila : Derni\u00e8re Danse, la vid\u00e9o lyrics d\u00e9voil\u00e9e|work=Melty|language=French|accessdate=13 November 2013}}</ref> The video starts off with the title and a sketched version of the singer and a fade-out to black after the song finishes. There is also a Germany-only re-release of the music video provided with German subtitles released after the premiere of the original music video.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vevo.com/watch/indila/dernire-danse-german-subtitles/FRUV71400086?gclid=CNXLuYzzgL0CFWT4wgod9SIAoQ|title=Derni\u00e8re Danse (German Subtitles) \u2013 Indila \u2013 Vevo|work=[[Vevo]]}}</ref>\n\n== Chart performance ==\nOn 1 March 2014, it entered the Greek charts at number-one and stayed at the first place for seven weeks.<ref name=\"greekcharts1\"/> On 19 April 2014, it was knocked down to No. 2 by [[Pharrell Williams]]' [[Happy (Pharrell Williams song)|Happy]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/biz/charts/2014-04-19/greece|title=''Billboard'' Greece Digital Songs \u2013 April 19, 2014|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=12 April 2014|accessdate=10 July 2014}}</ref> It reclaimed No. 1 the following week,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/biz/charts/2014-04-26/greece|title=''Billboard'' Greece Digital Songs \u2013 April 26, 2014|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=19 April 2014|accessdate=10 July 2014}}</ref> and remained there for another five weeks, totaling at thirteen weeks at No. 1.<ref name=\"greekcharts4\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/biz/charts/2014-05-31/greece|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|title=Greece Digital Songs \u2013 May 31, 2014}} {{subscription required}}</ref>\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n=== Weekly charts ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"|Chart (2014)\n!scope=\"col\"|Peak<br>position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" {{singlechart|Austria|72|artist=Indila|song=Derni\u00e8re danse}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" {{singlechart|Flanders|5|artist=Indila|song=Derni\u00e8re danse}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" {{singlechart|Wallonia|2|artist=Indila|song=Derni\u00e8re danse}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Belgium Digital Songs (''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'')<ref name=\"belgiancharts1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/biz/charts/2014-03-08/belgium|title=Belgium Digital Songs \u2013 March 8, 2014|date=8 March 2014|accessdate=10 June 2014}} {{subscription required}}</ref>\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"| 4\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" {{singlechart|Czech Republic|24|week=27|year=2014}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" {{singlechart|Czechdigital|53|year=2014|week=33|accessdate=August 19, 2014}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" {{singlechart|France|2|artist=Indila|song=Derni\u00e8re danse}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" {{singlechart|Germany2|47|artist=Indila|song=Derni\u00e8re danse|songid=1216653|accessdate=16 May 2019}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Greece Airplay Chart ([[International Federation of the Phonographic Industry|IFPI]])<ref>{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140417074230/http://www.ifpi.gr/airplay_el.html|url=http://www.ifpi.gr/airplay_el.html|title=Airplay Chart|language=Greek|publisher=[[International Federation of the Phonographic Industry]]|archivedate=17 April 2014}}</ref>\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Greece Digital Songs (''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'')<ref name=\"greekcharts1\">{{cite web|url=http